Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["explanation", "Subsubsection",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.674561656760564*^9, 3.674561657333578*^9}, {
  3.674562537059839*^9, 3.674562537597806*^9}, {3.674563295641884*^9, 
  3.6745632972273216`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"66e3b559-0135-4e49-8158-\
67138f3bf493"],

Cell["\<\
Suppose the density operator is diagonal in the singlet-triplet space with \
elements (+(3\[CapitalDelta]/4),-\[CapitalDelta]/4,-\[CapitalDelta]/4,-\
\[CapitalDelta]/4 0,0...)+(1/4)Unity, where the zeros are repeated dim/4 \
times, where dim is the dimension of the Hilbert space. Here (dim/4) is the \
dimension of the Hilbert subspace excluding the spin-1/2 pair. 
The singlet-triplet population imbalance is (3\[CapitalDelta]/4)-(-\
\[CapitalDelta]/4) = \[CapitalDelta]. The expression OperatorAmplitude[\[Rho]\
\[Rule]SingletPolarizationLevelOperator[]] should therefore give the result \
\[CapitalDelta] in this case. 

Assume that SingletPolarizationLevelOperator[{j,k}] = \[Kappa] opI[j].opI[k]. \
The matrix representation of this operator is given by SPLO = diagmatrix[(\
\[Kappa]/4){-3,1,1,1 ...}] repeating the first 4 elements (dim/4) times. The \
norm-squared of this operator is |SPLO|^2 = (\[Kappa]/4)^2 (3^2 + 3 ) (dim/4) \
= \[Kappa]^2 (12/16)(dim/4) = \[Kappa]^2 (3 dim/16) 

OperatorAmplitude[\[Rho]\[Rule]SPLO] evaluates to (\[Rho] |SPLO )/(SPLO/SPLO) \
which should give \[CapitalDelta] in the case above. 
Hence ((3\[CapitalDelta]/4)(-3\[Kappa]/4) + \
3(-\[CapitalDelta]/4)(\[Kappa]/4)) /( \[Kappa]^2 (3 dim/16) )  = \
\[CapitalDelta].
Hence \[CapitalDelta] (-9\[Kappa] - 3\[Kappa] ) / ( \[Kappa]^2 3 dim ) =    \
\[CapitalDelta]
and therefore \[Kappa] = -12/(3 dim) = -(4/dim).

Hence SingletPolarizationLevelOperator[{j,k}]  = -(4/dim)opI[j].opI[k]\
\>", "Text",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.674563307161563*^9, 3.674563421417411*^9}, {
  3.674563464314994*^9, 3.674563628509603*^9}, {3.674563659357161*^9, 
  3.67456451231903*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"efe6f81b-cd18-40cd-9763-\
6b1a663dacb2"]
}, Closed]]
}, Closed]],

